The paper deals with semantic image retrieval, which involves understanding the content of images and retrieving them based on their semantic meaning. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also describes the use of machine learning models to capture the visual features and spatial relationships of objects in images, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of scores to rank images in a collection, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to describe visual situations, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
